 The team at Explore Learning sent HuffPost UK six previous questions that have previously appeared on actual SATs exams. How many can you answer correctly? Can you pass me the salt?  Both of the ______ climbed up on to the roof. :: workman :: workmens :: workmans :: workmen  It was the scariest film she had ever seen. He threw his new toys carelessly into the box. They play football there.     Answers below the picture. 1. 'Pass me the salt.' or 'Pass me the salt!' 2. Workmen 3. Ever, carelessly and there 4. 95cm 5. 4, 12, 36 6. 226g or 0.226kg Share this slide: